OL,3,CMigrant workers in Jersey 'threatened
OL,4,Cand scared to speak up'
OL,6,FA migrant claims temporary workers
OL,7,Flike him face threats, racism and
OL,8,Fmistreatment while in Jersey.
OL,10,FSpeaking anonymously about his role in
OL,11,Fhospitality, he says: "I feel no
OL,12,Ffreedom, you only stick to your
OL,13,Fworkplace and your accommodation, that
OL,14,Fis it.
OL,16,F"People can't speak up openly because
OL,17,Fthey are threatened, 'I will not allow
OL,18,Fyou to come next year if you don't do
OL,19,Fwhat I'm telling you'.
