OL,6,FMore than 60 different nationalities
OL,7,Ftravelled to work in Jersey
OL,8,Ftemporarily last year, with the
OL,9,Fhighest number of workers from Kenya,
OL,10,Fthe Philippines and India.
OL,12,FAcross the island, there were 459
OL,13,Femployers responsible for bringing
OL,14,Ftemporary workers into the island.
OL,16,FModern slavery is defined as when an
OL,17,Findividual is exploited by others for
OL,18,Fpersonal or commercial gain. It covers
OL,19,Fwhether they are tricked, coerced,
OL,20,Fforced, or lose their freedom.
