OL,6,FThe Minister adds: "In the coming
OL,7,Fweeks, over the summer recess, I will
OL,8,Fbe making arrangements to speak to a
OL,9,Fcontact in the UK who I wish to meet
OL,10,Fregarding the issue of modern slavery.
OL,12,F"If an individual was held in
OL,13,Fconditions amounting to modern
OL,14,Fslavery, it is very likely that
OL,15,Falternative charges could be made,
OL,16,Fpotentially related to the unlawful
OL,17,Fdetention of a person, or their
OL,18,Ftreatment under employment law.
OL,20,F"Any reports made of this nature would
OL,21,Fbe thoroughly investigated.
